===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[βόμβος]]''' (''bombos'') "booming, humming, buzzing" (imitative of the sound itself).

===Usage Notes===
To tell the difference between the two [[diametrical]] slang meanings of ''bomb'', examine the article : for "a failure", the phrase used is generally "a bomb"; for "a success", the phrase used is generally "the bomb".

